import pandas as pd
import os
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

# Define the base directory for cloudbed-1 on March 21, 2022
base_dir = 'dataset/Market/cloudbed-1/telemetry/2022_03_21/metric/'

# Read the service metric data
service_metric_path = os.path.join(base_dir, 'metric_service.csv')
service_metric_df = pd.read_csv(service_metric_path)

# Convert timestamp to datetime (UTC+8)
service_metric_df['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(service_metric_df['timestamp'], unit='s').dt.tz_localize('UTC').dt.tz_convert('Asia/Hong_Kong')

# Define the failure time range: March 21, 2022 02:00-02:30 UTC+8
start_time = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 2, 0, 0, tzinfo=pd.Timestamp.now().tz)
end_time = datetime(2022, 3, 21, 2, 30, 0, tzinfo=pd.Timestamp.now().tz)

# Filter data for the failure time range
failure_service_metric_df = service_metric_df[(service_metric_df['datetime'] >= start_time) & (service_metric_df['datetime'] <= end_time)]

# Calculate global thresholds for each KPI using all data in the file
global_thresholds = {
    'rr': {'p5': service_metric_df['rr'].quantile(0.05), 'p95': service_metric_df['rr'].quantile(0.95)},
    'sr': {'p5': service_metric_df['sr'].quantile(0.05), 'p95': service_metric_df['sr'].quantile(0.95)},
    'mrt': {'p5': service_metric_df['mrt'].quantile(0.05), 'p95': service_metric_df['mrt'].quantile(0.95)},
    'count': {'p5': service_metric_df['count'].quantile(0.05), 'p95': service_metric_df['count'].quantile(0.95)}
}

# Identify anomalies in the failure time range
anomalies = []
for service in failure_service_metric_df['service'].unique():
    service_data = failure_service_metric_df[failure_service_metric_df['service'] == service]
    for idx, row in service_data.iterrows():
        anomaly = {'service': service, 'datetime': row['datetime']}
        
        # Check RR anomalies (request rate)
        if row['rr'] <= global_thresholds['rr']['p5'] or row['rr'] >= global_thresholds['rr']['p95']:
            anomaly['rr'] = f"{row['rr']:.2f} (threshold: p5={global_thresholds['rr']['p5']:.2f}, p95={global_thresholds['rr']['p95']:.2f})"
        
        # Check SR anomalies (success rate)
        if row['sr'] <= global_thresholds['sr']['p5'] or row['sr'] >= global_thresholds['sr']['p95']:
            anomaly['sr'] = f"{row['sr']:.2f} (threshold: p5={global_thresholds['sr']['p5']:.2f}, p95={global_thresholds['sr']['p95']:.2f})"
        
        # Check MRT anomalies (mean response time)
        if row['mrt'] <= global_thresholds['mrt']['p5'] or row['mrt'] >= global_thresholds['mrt']['p95']:
            anomaly['mrt'] = f"{row['mrt']:.2f} (threshold: p5={global_thresholds['mrt']['p5']:.2f}, p95={global_thresholds['mrt']['p95']:.2f})"
        
        # Check Count anomalies (request count)
        if row['count'] <= global_thresholds['count']['p5'] or row['count'] >= global_thresholds['count']['p95']:
            anomaly['count'] = f"{row['count']:.2f} (threshold: p5={global_thresholds['count']['p5']:.2f}, p95={global_thresholds['count']['p95']:.2f})"
        
        if len(anomaly) > 2:  # If any anomaly was found
            anomalies.append(anomaly)

# Print the results
print("Global Thresholds:")
for kpi, thresholds in global_thresholds.items():
    print(f"  {kpi}: p5={thresholds['p5']:.2f}, p95={thresholds['p95']:.2f}")

print("\nAnomalies detected between 02:00 and 02:30 UTC+8:")
for anomaly in anomalies:
    print(f"\nService: {anomaly['service']}")
    print(f"  Time: {anomaly['datetime']}")
    for kpi, value in anomaly.items():
        if kpi not in ['service', 'datetime']:
            print(f"  {kpi}: {value}")
